<font color="#FF0000">TO THE FUTURE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Feb 21 20:38:36 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I watched this site since its beginning and even though asked to be with it from the start abstained.  I was content to read occasionally but not tempted to participate.  When the Forum was created I was again asked to be a part and again I abstained feeling I didn't belong to this group.  After all it was a &quot;Slice of Americana&quot;, the Vets and Protestors could continue without me.  I felt no pain, emotion, or guilt.  I didn't need the dialogue I wasn't searching for anything.<br><br>
At some point after numerous suggestions from Art, I posted.  I have never regretted the decision.  I have had the chance to grow and understand that it wasn't only the Vietnam War that had effected me but the summation of an entire working life in the defense arena, which I continue to this day.  I came to grips with my emotions or rather the lack of them and received advice from the many on this site.  I can not thank each individually for fear of leaving someone out.<br><br>
This has been a life experience interacting with all perspectives.  I have grown and made friends here, many of which I will maintain for life.  With the wisdom that existed on these pages we were all able to receive more than we gave.  It is not often these opportunities are available and I thank the hosts and Mark Weiss for their dedication in sustaining their vision through the good times and the bad.<br><br>
I make this last post with both reluctance and optimism.  From this seed there are greater things to come.  I am willing to take the risk.  To the future.<br>

